Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Back Then..
Author: BIRKENHEAD CITY COUNCIL
Vol / Page: I : 19
Edition:
Quote: When you picked [strawberries] you had a little wooden carrier with three chips in it. One was for the jam berries and the other two were for berries that you were picking and you packed as you went...They were a ply. Very thin... It was a very light wood and very, very thin like a veneer.
Notes: This refers to about 1930

Date: 0/0/1980
Source: Personal Kiwi-Yankee Dictionary, A
Author: LELAND
Vol / Page: 25
Edition:
Quote: Chip. A North Island term for a SMALL BOX of berries, the equivalent of (see:) <i>punnet</i>, also a North Island term. The South Island term (Christchurch south), is (see:) <i>pottle. </i>
